						<summary>

						<p>Slab near the Girijavvana Gadduge.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalla [Jayasiṁha II] 11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record in the 11th century A.D. characters, states that <hi rend="italic">mahāsāmanta</hi> Lōkarasa of the Haihaya family made a land grant to the sculptor Nēmōja at Moṟaba. Lōkarasa is described as the son of Chālukya king Jagadēkamalla.</p>						

